Downloaded

  README.md
  Inter-3.15.zip

from https://github.com/rsms/inter/

  unzip Inter-3.15.zip

Copied Inter Desktop/Inter-*.otf to a working directory.

  otfinfo -f Inter-Regular.otf

to see what features are available (and which features are
*not*). The Inter fonts provide proportional and tabular
figures (presumably lining), subscripts and superscripts.

The License does not reserve the Inter font name so it won't
be necessary to re-name the (derived) fonts.

  autoinst -target=texmf -vendor=public -typeface=inter -encoding=OT1,T1,TS1,LY1 *.otf

inter.log tells us:

NFSS mappings:

    ul  =>  thin
    el  =>  extralight
    l   =>  light
    sl  =>  
    m   =>  regular
    sb  =>  semibold
    b   =>  bold
    eb  =>  extrabold
    ub  =>  black

    uc  =>  
    ec  =>  
    c   =>  
    sc  =>  
    m   =>  regular
    sx  =>  
    x   =>  
    ex  =>  
    ux  =>  

Note that there is no mapping for Medium (because m is
mapped to Regular).

Check that pfbs are generated in
texmf/fonts/type1/public/inter (otftotfm sometimes fails to
do that).

  mkdir -p texmf/fonts/opentype/public/inter

  cp *.otf texmf/fonts/opentype/public/inter

  zip -r inter.tds.zip fonts tex
  mv inter.tds.zip ~/texmf
  cd ~/texmf
  unzip inter.tds.zip
  texhash .
  updmap-user --enable Map Inter.map

I now create a rudimentary test file inter-samples.tex and
check that all is well:

_________________________________________________________

\documentclass{article}
\usepackage[T1]{fontenc}
\usepackage{Inter}
\usepackage{lipsum}
\begin{document}

\subsection*{Regular}
\lipsum[1]


\subsection*{Bold}

\textbf{\lipsum[2]}


\subsection*{Italic}

\textit{\lipsum[3]}

\subsection*{Bold Italic}


\textbf{\textit{\lipsum[4]}}

\subsection*{Default Numbers}

1234567890

\subsection*{Superscripts}

X{\sufigures 1234567890}

\end{document}

_______________________________________________________


I now create a more refined style file inter.sty which is
to replace the autoinst-generated Inter.sty:

___________________________________________________________________________

\NeedsTeXFormat{LaTeX2e}
\ProvidesPackage{inter}
    [2020/12/13 (Bob Tennent and autoinst)  Style file for Inter fonts.]

\RequirePackage{iftex,xkeyval,textcomp}

\newif\ifinter@tabular \inter@tabularfalse

\newif\ifinter@medium  \inter@mediumfalse
\newif\ifinter@semibold  \inter@semiboldfalse
\newif\ifinter@extrabold  \inter@extraboldfalse
\newif\ifinter@heavy  \inter@heavyfalse
\newif\ifinter@light  \inter@lightfalse
\newif\ifinter@extralight  \inter@extralightfalse
\newif\ifinter@thin  \inter@thinfalse
\newif\ifinter@default \inter@defaultfalse

\newcommand*{\Inter@scale}{1}
\RequirePackage{xkeyval}
\DeclareOptionX{scaled}{\renewcommand*{\Inter@scale}{#1}}
\DeclareOptionX{scale}{\renewcommand*{\Inter@scale}{#1}}
\DeclareOptionX{type1}{\inter@otffalse}
\DeclareOptionX{lining}{\inter@liningtrue}
\DeclareOptionX{tabular}{\inter@tabulartrue}
\DeclareOptionX{t}{\inter@tabulartrue}

\DeclareOptionX{medium}{\inter@mediumtrue}
\DeclareOptionX{mb}{\inter@mediumtrue}
\DeclareOptionX{semibold}{\inter@semiboldtrue}
\DeclareOptionX{sb}{\inter@semiboldtrue}
\DeclareOptionX{light}{\inter@lighttrue}
\DeclareOptionX{l}{\inter@lighttrue}
\DeclareOptionX{extralight}{\inter@extralighttrue}
\DeclareOptionX{thin}{\inter@thintrue}
\DeclareOptionX{extrabold}{\inter@extraboldtrue}
\DeclareOptionX{heavy}{\inter@heavytrue}
\DeclareOptionX{default}{\inter@defaulttrue}
\DeclareOptionX{sfdefault}{\inter@defaulttrue}


\ProcessOptionsX

\ifinter@tabular
  \def\inter@figurealign{T}
\else
  \def\inter@figurealign{}
\fi

\def\bfseries@sf{b}
\ifinter@semibold\def\bfseries@sf{sb}\fi
\ifinter@extrabold\def\bfseries@sf{eb}\fi
\ifinter@heavy\def\bfseries@sf{ub}\fi

\def\mdseries@sf{m}
\ifinter@medium\def\mdseries@sf{medium}\fi
\ifinter@light\def\mdseries@sf{l}\fi
\ifinter@extralight\def\mdseries@sf{el}\fi
\ifinter@thin\def\mdseries@sf{ul}\fi


\def\inter@family{Inter-\inter@figurealign LF}
\renewcommand*\sfdefault{\inter@family}
\ifinter@default\edef\familydefault{\sfdefault}\edef\seriesdefault{\mdseries@sf}\fi

\fa@naming@exception{figures}{{superior}{proportional}}{Sup}
\fa@naming@exception{figures}{{superior}{tabular}}{Sup}
\def\sufigures{\@nomath\sufigures\fontfigurestyle{superior}\selectfont}

\def\intertabular{\fontfamily{Inter-TLF}\selectfont}
\def\interproportional{\fontfamily{Inter-LF}\selectfont}

\def\interthin{\fontfamily{\inter@family}\fontseries{thin}\selectfont}
\def\interlight{\fontfamily{\inter@family}\fontseries{l}\selectfont}
\def\interextralight{\fontfamily{\inter@family}\fontseries{el}\selectfont}
\def\intermedium{\fontfamily{\inter@family}\fontseries{medium}\selectfont}
\def\intersemibold{\fontfamily{\inter@family}\fontseries{sb}\selectfont}
\def\interextrabold{\fontfamily{\inter@family}\fontseries{eb}\selectfont}
\def\interheavy{\fontfamily{\inter@family}\fontseries{ub}\selectfont}

\endinput

________________________________________________________________________________________

and a more elaborate test file:

________________________________________________________________________________________

\documentclass{article}
\usepackage[T1]{fontenc}
\usepackage[sfdefault]{inter}
\usepackage{lipsum}
\begin{document}

\subsection*{Regular}
\lipsum[1]


\subsection*{Bold}

\textbf{\lipsum[2]}


\subsection*{Italic}

\textit{\lipsum[3]}

\subsection*{Bold Italic}

\textbf{\textit{\lipsum[4]}}


\subsection*{Thin}

{\interthin \lipsum[5]}

\subsection*{Light}

{\interlight \lipsum[6]}

\subsection*{Extra Light}

{\interextralight \lipsum[7]}

\subsection*{Medium}
{\intermedium \lipsum[8]}

\subsection*{Semi Bold}
{\intersemibold \lipsum[9]}

\subsection*{Extra Bold}
{\interextrabold\lipsum[10]}

\subsection*{Heavy}
{\interheavy\lipsum[11]}

\subsection*{Default Numbers}

1234567890

\subsection*{Tabular Numbers}
{\intertabular 1234567890}

\subsection*{Proportional Numbers}
{\interproportional 1234567890}

\subsection*{Superscripts}

X{\sufigures 1234567890}

\end{document}

______________________________________________________________________________________


Then I add xe/lua-latex support to inter.sty:

______________________________________________________________________________________


\NeedsTeXFormat{LaTeX2e}
\ProvidesPackage{inter}
    [2020/12/13 (Bob Tennent and autoinst)  Style file for Inter fonts.]

\RequirePackage{iftex,xkeyval,textcomp}

\newif\ifinter@otf 
\ifxetex
  \inter@otftrue
\else\ifluatex
  \inter@otftrue
\else  % [pdf]LaTeX
  \inter@otffalse
\fi\fi

\newif\ifinter@tabular \inter@tabularfalse

\newif\ifinter@medium  \inter@mediumfalse
\newif\ifinter@semibold  \inter@semiboldfalse
\newif\ifinter@extrabold  \inter@extraboldfalse
\newif\ifinter@heavy  \inter@heavyfalse
\newif\ifinter@light  \inter@lightfalse
\newif\ifinter@extralight  \inter@extralightfalse
\newif\ifinter@thin  \inter@thinfalse
\newif\ifinter@default \inter@defaultfalse

\newcommand*{\Inter@scale}{1}
\RequirePackage{xkeyval}
\DeclareOptionX{scaled}{\renewcommand*{\Inter@scale}{#1}}
\DeclareOptionX{scale}{\renewcommand*{\Inter@scale}{#1}}
\DeclareOptionX{type1}{\inter@otffalse}
\DeclareOptionX{lining}{\inter@liningtrue}
\DeclareOptionX{tabular}{\inter@tabulartrue}
\DeclareOptionX{t}{\inter@tabulartrue}

\DeclareOptionX{medium}{\inter@mediumtrue}
\DeclareOptionX{mb}{\inter@mediumtrue}
\DeclareOptionX{semibold}{\inter@semiboldtrue}
\DeclareOptionX{sb}{\inter@semiboldtrue}
\DeclareOptionX{light}{\inter@lighttrue}
\DeclareOptionX{l}{\inter@lighttrue}
\DeclareOptionX{extralight}{\inter@extralighttrue}
\DeclareOptionX{thin}{\inter@thintrue}
\DeclareOptionX{extrabold}{\inter@extraboldtrue}
\DeclareOptionX{heavy}{\inter@heavytrue}
\DeclareOptionX{default}{\inter@defaulttrue}
\DeclareOptionX{sfdefault}{\inter@defaulttrue}


\ProcessOptionsX

\ifinter@otf
  \ifinter@tabular
    \def\inter@otffigurealign{Monospaced} 
  \else
    \def\inter@otffigurealign{Proportional} 
  \fi

\else % type1

\ifinter@tabular
  \def\inter@figurealign{T}
\else
  \def\inter@figurealign{}
\fi

\fi

\ifinter@otf
  \def\inter@boldstyle{Bold}
  \ifinter@semibold\def\inter@boldstyle{SemiBold}\fi
  \ifinter@extrabold\def\inter@boldstyle{ExtraBold}\fi
  \ifinter@heavy\def\inter@boldstyle{Black}\fi

  \def\inter@regstyle{Regular}
  \ifinter@medium\def\inter@regstyle{Medium}\fi
  \ifinter@light\def\inter@regstyle{Light}\fi
  \ifinter@extralight\def\inter@regstyle{ExtraLight}\fi
  \ifinter@thin\def\inter@regstyle{Thin}\fi

\else % type1

  \def\bfseries@sf{b}
  \ifinter@semibold\def\bfseries@sf{sb}\fi
  \ifinter@extrabold\def\bfseries@sf{eb}\fi
  \ifinter@heavy\def\bfseries@sf{ub}\fi

  \def\mdseries@sf{m}
  \ifinter@medium\def\mdseries@sf{medium}\fi
  \ifinter@light\def\mdseries@sf{l}\fi
  \ifinter@extralight\def\mdseries@sf{el}\fi
  \ifinter@thin\def\mdseries@sf{ul}\fi
\fi


\ifinter@otf
  \RequirePackage{fontspec}
\else
  \RequirePackage{mweights,fontaxes}
\fi

\ifinter@otf
  \def\inter@regular{Regular}
  \ifxetex\XeTeXtracingfonts=1\fi
  \defaultfontfeatures{
        Ligatures = TeX ,
        Scale     = \Inter@scale ,
        Extension = .otf }
  \setsansfont
      [ Numbers = {\inter@otffigurealign},
        UprightFont    = *-\inter@regstyle ,
        ItalicFont = *-\ifx\inter@regstyle\inter@regular\else\inter@regstyle\fi Italic,
        BoldFont    = *-\inter@boldstyle ,
        BoldItalicFont     = *-\inter@boldstyle Italic ,
      ]
      {Inter}
  % grab current family in case of subsequent change:
  \let\interfamily\sfdefault  
  \ifinter@default\renewcommand*\familydefault{\interfamily}\fi

  \providecommand\sufigures{\addfontfeatures{VerticalPosition=Superior}}
  \newfontfamily\intertabular
    [ Numbers = {Monospaced},
        UprightFont    = *-\inter@regstyle ,
        ItalicFont = *-\ifx\inter@regstyle\inter@regular\else\inter@regstyle\fi Italic,
        BoldFont    = *-\inter@boldstyle ,
        BoldItalicFont     = *-\inter@boldstyle Italic ,
    ]
    {Inter}
  \newfontfamily\interproportional
    [ Numbers = {Proportional},
        UprightFont    = *-\inter@regstyle ,
        ItalicFont = *-\ifx\inter@regstyle\inter@regular\else\inter@regstyle\fi Italic,
        BoldFont    = *-\inter@boldstyle ,
        BoldItalicFont     = *-\inter@boldstyle Italic ,
    ]
    {Inter}
  \newfontfamily\interthin
      [ Numbers = {\inter@otffigurealign},
        UprightFont    = *-Thin ,
        ItalicFont     = *-ThinItalic ,
        BoldFont    = *-\inter@boldstyle ,
        BoldItalicFont     = *-\inter@boldstyle Italic ,
      ]
      {Inter}
  \newfontfamily\interlight
      [ Numbers = {\inter@otffigurealign},
        UprightFont    = *-Light ,
        ItalicFont     = *-LightItalic ,
        BoldFont    = *-\inter@boldstyle ,
        BoldItalicFont     = *-\inter@boldstyle Italic ,
      ]
      {Inter}
  \newfontfamily\interextralight
      [ Numbers = {\inter@otffigurealign},
        UprightFont    = *-ExtraLight ,
        ItalicFont     = *-ExtraLightItalic ,
        BoldFont    = *-\inter@boldstyle ,
        BoldItalicFont     = *-\inter@boldstyle Italic ,
      ]
      {Inter}
  \newfontfamily\intermedium
      [ Numbers = {\inter@otffigurealign},
        UprightFont    = *-Medium ,
        ItalicFont     = *-MediumItalic ,
        BoldFont    = *-\inter@boldstyle ,
        BoldItalicFont     = *-\inter@boldstyle Italic ,
      ]
      {Inter}
  \newfontfamily\intersemibold
      [ Numbers = {\inter@otffigurealign},
        UprightFont    = *-SemiBold ,
        ItalicFont     = *-SemiBoldItalic ,
      ]
      {Inter}
  \newfontfamily\interextrabold
      [ Numbers = {\inter@otffigurealign},
        UprightFont    = *-ExtraBold ,
        ItalicFont     = *-ExtraBoldItalic ,
      ]
      {Inter}
  \newfontfamily\interheavy
      [ Numbers = {\inter@otffigurealign},
        UprightFont    = *-Black ,
        ItalicFont     = *-BlackItalic ,
      ]
      {Inter}

\else % type1


  \def\inter@family{Inter-\inter@figurealign LF}
  \renewcommand*\sfdefault{\inter@family}
  \ifinter@default\edef\familydefault{\sfdefault}\edef\seriesdefault{\mdseries@sf}\fi

  \fa@naming@exception{figures}{{superior}{proportional}}{Sup}
  \fa@naming@exception{figures}{{superior}{tabular}}{Sup}
  \def\sufigures{\@nomath\sufigures\fontfigurestyle{superior}\selectfont}

  \def\intertabular{\fontfamily{Inter-TLF}\selectfont}
  \def\interproportional{\fontfamily{Inter-LF}\selectfont}

  \def\interthin{\fontfamily{\inter@family}\fontseries{thin}\selectfont}
  \def\interlight{\fontfamily{\inter@family}\fontseries{l}\selectfont}
  \def\interextralight{\fontfamily{\inter@family}\fontseries{el}\selectfont}
  \def\intermedium{\fontfamily{\inter@family}\fontseries{medium}\selectfont}
  \def\intersemibold{\fontfamily{\inter@family}\fontseries{sb}\selectfont}
  \def\interextrabold{\fontfamily{\inter@family}\fontseries{eb}\selectfont}
  \def\interheavy{\fontfamily{\inter@family}\fontseries{ub}\selectfont}

\fi

\ifinter@otf
  \defaultfontfeatures{}
\fi

\endinput
 _________________________________________________________________________________________

and verify that the inter-samples.tex test file can be
successfully processed by xelatex and lualatex.

At this point, Inter.sty in texmf/tex/latex/inter can be
replaced by inter.sty.


Now start to create the documentation:

  mkdir -p texmf/doc/fonts/inter
  cp LICENSE.txt README.md texmf/doc/fonts/inter

I do 
  
  dos2unix LICENSE.txt README.md 

in case line terminations are Windows-like.

  cp inter-samples.tex inter-samples.pdf texmf/doc/fonts/inter

Then create a README file for the CTAN package:

_________________________________________________________________________________________

This is the README for the inter package, version 2020/12/13.

This package provides LaTeX, pdfLaTeX, XeLaTeX and LuaLaTeX
support for the Inter Sans family of fonts (version 3.015),
designed by Rasmus Andersson. Inter is a typeface specially
designed for user interfaces with focus on high legibility
of small-to-medium sized text on computer screens. The
family features a tall x-height to aid in readability of
mixed-case and lower-case text.

To install this package on a TDS-compliant TeX system
download the file "tex-archive"/install/fonts/inter.tds.zip
where the preferred URL for "tex-archive" is
http://mirrors.ctan.org. Unzip the archive at the root
of an appropriate texmf tree, likely a personal or local
tree. If necessary, update the file-name database (e.g.,
texhash). Update the font-map files by enabling the Map file
Inter.map.

To use, add

\usepackage{inter}

to the preamble of your document. These will activate Inter
as the sans-serif text font. To activate it as the main text
font, use

\usepackage[sfdefault]{inter}

LuaLaTeX and xeLaTeX users who might prefer type1 fonts or
who wish to avoid fontspec may use the type1 option.

Options scaled=<number> or scale=<number> may be used to
scale the fonts.

The default figure style is proportional-lining, but the
tabular (or t) option will change the default to tabular
(monospaced) figures.

Font encodings supported are OT1, T1, TS1, and LY1.

The semibold, extrabold and heavy options activate those
series as the default bold series. The medium, light,
extralight and thin options activate those series as the
default regular series.

Commands \intertabular, and \interproportional allow for
localized use of non-default figures. Superior numbers are
available using \sufigures. Commands \interthin, \interlight
etc. allow for localized use of those series.

The original OpenType fonts were obtained from

https://github.com/rsms/inter/

and are licensed under the SIL Open Font License, version
1.1; the text may be found in the doc directory. The type1
versions were created using cfftot1. The support files were
created using autoinst and are licensed under the terms of
the LaTeX Project Public License. The maintainer of this
package is Bob Tennent at rdt(at)cs(dot)queensu(dot)ca.

____________________________________________________________

and copy to texmf/doc/fonts/inter

Finally 

  zip -r inter.tds.zip fonts tex doc
  cp inter.tds.zip  ~/texmf
  cd ~/texmf
  rm -rf `find . -name inter -print 2> /dev/null`
  unzip inter.tds.zip
  texhash .
  updmap-user 

and verify that the test file is correctly processed.

The final step is to create a CTAN-ready package but I'll
stop here for now.


Best,
Bob








